00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,848
If you're switching from service-based to product-based, THIS is the stuff you need to know.

2
00:00:04,798 --> 00:00:12,163
And get this,  kafka's consumer model is pull-based: consumers call poll() on their own schedule, at their own rate.

3
00:00:12,163 --> 00:00:19,500
This decouples consumer speed from producer speed and allows consumers to process at whatever pace their application requires.

4
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:26,153
Mastering the consumer group protocol, offset management, and the poll loop is essential for building reliable consumers.

5
00:00:26,153 --> 00:00:29,115
Everyone says The Poll Loop is the best approach.

6
00:00:29,115 --> 00:00:32,480
That is , actually wrong for most real-world systems.

7
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:34,692
I will show you why in a moment.

